Aprroach 2: BFS Graph coloring




graph colouring
each state (m,c,t)  -> represent a node
there will be 3 colors  M-->1    C-->2    D-->0  each node will be colored in one of these color

if node (m,c,t) have color M-> this mean that if cat and mouse reach this state the mouse win
if node (m,c,t) have color C-> this mean that if cat and mouse reach this state the cat win

but initially we know the color of some nodes

```
