for making it lexographically smaller non-palindromic after replacing a character , we will simply look for a character which is not 'a' from i=0 to i<n/2 .
1.If such character exists , we will simply put palindrome[i]='a' and exists out of the loop while making flag=1 (there is such character exists)
2. If such character doesn't exist then flag will remain equal to 0 .In this case , we will simply put palinrome[n-1]='a';
