#### Intuition
1. To make the string lexicographically smallest, first preference will be given to add 'a' to the string. If 'a' is there then add 'b' and so on..
2. To break a palindrome replace characters.
3. Combine both 1 + 2 points.

#### Approach
Case -01 : racecar
Iterate till the middle and see if 'a' is present or not. If not then add it to make it lexico. smallest. We get, 'aacecar'.

Case-02 : aaaaa
Iterate till middle, since all characters are 'a' therefore, next half will also be filled with 'a'. Now, to make it lexico. smallest just add 'b' to the end of string. We get, 'aaaab'.

Case-03 : b
Single character is considered a palindrome, so we can't break it. Just return `" "`


