The problem is not that hard. Since we have to replace one character. The only thing that makes this question slightly challenging is the lexiographical order the answer expects.

# Approach
We need to iterate till the half. If there is any char that is other than 'a' simply replace it with 'a' and return string.

If all the char till mid are 'a', then replace the last char with 'b'

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(n)

